The test262 conformance slice — what it is and why each region is here.

This is a *curated starter slice* (~419 cases) of the official tc39/test262 ECMAScript
spec suite, run on the Porffor→Washy WASM→BEAM **ASM transpiler lane** — the shipping lane
that runs untrusted JS *emulated in WASM* (the EMULATION THESIS). The full ~50k-case suite
stays in the gitignored clone `nexus/.test262/`; this committed slice is small on purpose so
the `:test262` gate runs cheaply and never wedges CI.

The blocks below ARE the source of truth for the slice (NO JSON sidecar). Re-vendor with
`mix run scripts/test262-vendor-slice.exs`; probe an arbitrary larger area off the full clone
with `mix test262 <subdir>`.

manifest :test262_slice do
  region "language/statements/for-of",
    why: "iteration protocol — the for-of desugar + iterator stepping the ladder leans on"

  region "language/statements/for-in",
    why: "enumeration protocol — property visitation order + prototype-chain walk"

  region "language/statements/let",
    why: "TDZ + block scoping; closure-capture-by-binding (our recurring per-binding bug)"

  region "language/statements/const",
    why: "const binding immutability + TDZ, same closure-capture region as let"

  region "language/statements/for",
    why: "head-*-fresh-binding-per-iteration: the per-iteration let/const binding tests — the exact closure-capture-by-binding bug the ladder keeps hitting"

  region "language/expressions/generators",
    why: "generator expressions — yield suspension; Porffor generators are EAGER (known gap)"

  region "language/expressions/yield",
    why: "yield/yield* semantics — delegation + return value threading"

  region "language/statements/generators",
    why: "generator declarations — same eager-generator frontier from the declaration side"

  region "built-ins/RegExp",
    why: "character classes / ranges — the CURRENT acorn regex-range frontier under active work"

  region "built-ins/RegExp/prototype",
    why: "exec/test/Symbol.* prototype methods — lastIndex + match-object shape"

  region "built-ins/BigInt",
    why: "bigint primitive + BigInt() coercion — a recent gap"

  region "built-ins/Proxy",
    why: "Proxy traps — a recent gap; probes whether meta-object protocol is emulated"
end

skiplist :test262_unsupported do
  reason flag: :module, why: "ES module loading not wired into the single-program lane yet"
  reason flag: :async, why: "true async suspension (doneprintHandle harness) needs the BEAM-fiber await — async corpus is still @tag :skip"
  reason flag: :raw, why: "raw cases run with no harness/prelude; the lane needs the cjs prelude shims"
end

Running notes :test262_isolation do
  note "SIGABRT under load",
    why: "running all 419 cases in ONE BEAM SIGABRTs (exit 134) — the no-GC cross-case memory accumulation the corpus docs + run_corpus.exs warn about. The :test262 gate + scripts/test262-run-isolated.exs run in small OS-isolated batches so a crashing batch is reported, not fatal."
  note "parse-phase SyntaxError mis-id — FIXED (wb-8p78.6)",
    why: "Two harness-side measurement bugs, now corrected. (1) Nexus.Porffor.Debug @error_types was OFF-BY-ONE vs the source of truth (compiler/types.js registerInternalType, replayed: Error=37, AggregateError=38, TypeError=39, ReferenceError=40, SyntaxError=41 … Test262Error=45 — the old 36-based map predated the __Porffor_Empty internal type); it also now masks TYPE_FLAGS (0x80|0x40) before lookup. (2) A parse-phase reject surfaces as a COMPILE failure (the engine refuses to emit a module), which was scored as a generic compile_error gap. The harness now classifies a compile failure whose stderr is a SyntaxError thrown from compiler/parse.js as the spec SyntaxError@parse — a PASS iff the test's negative {phase: parse, type: SyntaxError} matches BOTH type and phase. An infra/module-load SyntaxError (node:internal/modules) is excluded so a broken toolchain never produces a false pass."
end
